\cf2 May the God of Hope fill you will all Joy and peace as you trust in Him, so that you may overflow with hope by the power of the Holy Spirit  -  Rom 15:13\
\pard\pardeftab720\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \
\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls9\ilvl0\cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}This is Paul\'92s prayer as he is wrapping up a letter he is writing to a church in Rome.  \
{\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}His desire for his people is that is that they would be filled so much with the Hope of God it would overflow into their everyday existence.\
{\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}Does Hope overflow in your life?  Do the people who have interactions with you?  Do they walk away from you more hopeful or less?  \
{\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}We are made to overflow with the Love of God and the Hope of a preferred future\
{\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}Trust is the key \'96 if you\'92re a Debby Downer but you would say you\'92re a Christian\'85maybe there is a trust gap.  In the beginning we talked about a communication for many people but for you\'85maybe there is a gap of trust.\
{\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}You believe in God, you\'92re a good person.  You just don\'92t really trust Him.  Which means you don\'92t really step out in faith which means you don\'92t really see the works of God like others do.  There is a gap.\
{\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}This is what I believe\'85whether you\'92re gap is of silence or trust\'85you were made to be like this!\
\pard\pardeftab720\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \
